{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BnX4HH62wDkF2KzsHVDkbH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NcE3pn5PjUwC5de3aU1qKH","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"PLAN='# Elasticsearch Cluster Migration Plan\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-23  \n**Cluster:** es-cluster (namespace: elasticsearch)  \n**Status:** DRAFT — pending SRE lead review and approval. No changes applied.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State Inventory\n\n### 1.1 Cluster Identity\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Cluster name | es-cluster |\n| Cluster UUID | pAQpvcZkRei_1_g7cggQ5w |\n| Version | 8.11.1 |\n| Lucene version | 9.8.0 |\n| Build date | 2023-11-11 |\n| License | Basic (active) |\n| Health | GREEN |\n\n### 1.2 Topology\n| Pod | IP | Roles | Node attr.tier |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| es-cluster-0 | 10.244.0.100 | master, data, ingest | hot |\n| es-cluster-1 | 10.244.0.99  | master, data, ingest | hot |\n| es-cluster-2 | 10.244.0.101 | master, data, ingest | hot |\n\nAll three nodes are co-located masters, data nodes, and ingest nodes (no dedicated role separation).\n\n### 1.3 Kubernetes Resources (StatefulSet es-cluster)\n| Setting | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Replicas | 3 |\n| Image | docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1 |\n| Pod management policy | Parallel |\n| Update strategy | OnDelete |\n| CPU request / limit | 500m / 1 |\n| Memory request / limit | 1Gi / 2Gi |\n| JVM heap (Xms/Xmx) | 512m / 512m |\n| PVC per node | 5Gi (ReadWriteOnce) |\n| mmap | Disabled (node.store.allow_mmap: false) |\n| Discovery | Static seed hosts via headless Service DNS |\n\n### 1.4 Security Configuration (elasticsearch.yml)\n| Setting | Value | Risk |\n|---|---|---|\n| xpack.security.enabled | false | CRITICAL — unauthenticated access |\n| xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled | false | CRITICAL — plaintext HTTP |\n| xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled | false | CRITICAL — plaintext inter-node traffic |\n\n### 1.5 Live Cluster Settings\nPersistent settings: none (all defaults)  \nTransient settings: none (all defaults)\n\nKey defaults in effect:\n- cluster.max_shards_per_node: 1000\n- cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.low: 85%\n- cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.high: 90%\n- cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.flood_stage: 95%\n- action.destructive_requires_name: true\n- cluster.initial_master_nodes: [es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2]\n\n### 1.6 Indices\n| Index | Shards | Replicas | Docs | Non-default settings |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| audit-index | 3 primary | 1 | 0 | routing.allocation.require.tier=hot; routing.allocation.include._tier_preference=data_content |\n\nThe shard-level tier routing (`require.tier: hot`) is a **non-default, intentionally applied setting**. All six shards (3 primary + 3 replica) are currently STARTED and distributed across all three nodes.\n\n### 1.7 ILM Policies\nOnly built-in system policies are present:\n- `.monitoring-8-ilm-policy` (hot 3d rollover → warm forcemerge → delete at 3d)\n- `180-days-default` (hot 30d rollover → warm 2d → cold 30d → delete 180d)\n- Additional built-in Elastic stack policies (not in active use by any index or data stream)\n\nNo custom ILM policies are applied. The `audit-index` has no ILM policy assigned.\n\n### 1.8 Index Templates\nOnly built-in Elastic stack templates are present (.kibana-reporting, .monitoring-*, etc.). No custom user-defined templates were found.\n\n### 1.9 Pending Task Backlog\nAt inspection time: **58 pending cluster tasks** with max wait ~62s. For an otherwise-idle cluster with a single empty index, this is abnormal and should be investigated before any upgrade proceeds.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Pre-Upgrade Checklist (Gates — must all pass before proceeding)\n\n1. **Resolve pending task backlog.** Confirm `_cluster/health` shows `number_of_pending_tasks: 0` (or near zero) before beginning.\n2. **Confirm cluster GREEN.** Verify `_cluster/health` returns `\"status\": \"green\"` with zero unassigned shards.\n3. **Snapshot backup.** Register a snapshot repository and take a full snapshot of all indices. Confirm snapshot `SUCCESS` before touching anything.\n4. **Identify target version.** Decide whether the upgrade is intra-minor (8.11.x → 8.17.x / 8.18.x — currently latest 8.x) or a major bump (8.11.1 → 9.x). Note: upgrading directly from 8.11.1 to 9.x is supported (8.x → 9.x rolling upgrade path), but requires all indices to be created on 8.x (already met). Confirm the target image tag and pull it on all nodes before starting.\n5. **Review deprecation warnings.** Run `GET /_migration/deprecations` against 8.11.1 to surface any settings or index mappings that will break in the target version.\n6. **Document the 58 pending tasks.** Run `GET /_cluster/pending_tasks` and triage.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Required Configuration Changes\n\n### 3.1 CRITICAL — Enable Security (xpack.security)\n**Current state:** All security disabled — the cluster is fully open with no authentication, no TLS on HTTP or transport.  \n**Risk:** Any process with network access to port 9200 can read, modify, or delete all data.\n\n**Changes required in elasticsearch.yml (ConfigMap es-config):**\n```yaml\nxpack.security.enabled: true\nxpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: true\nxpack.security.http.ssl.keystore.path: certs/http.p12\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: true\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.keystore.path: certs/transport.p12\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.truststore.path: certs/transport.p12\n```\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n- Generate a CA and per-node certificates using `elasticsearch-certutil` (or cert-manager).\n- Mount certificates as a Kubernetes Secret into each pod at the path above.\n- Run `elasticsearch-setup-passwords auto` (or use the enrollment token flow) to set passwords for built-in users (elastic, kibana_system, logstash_system, etc.).\n- Update the readinessProbe in the StatefulSet from HTTP to HTTPS with credentials.\n- Any application or sidecar currently calling `http://es-http:9200` must be updated to use HTTPS with valid credentials.\n\n**Order:** This change must be co-ordinated with all consumers. Recommend enabling first on transport (inter-node), then HTTP, in a separate maintenance window.\n\n### 3.2 HIGH — Update Strategy: OnDelete → RollingUpdate\n**Current state:** `updateStrategy.type: OnDelete` means no pod is restarted automatically when the StatefulSet spec changes. Operators must manually delete pods one at a time to roll out a new image.  \n**Risk:** Easy to forget a pod and end up with a mixed-version cluster indefinitely.\n\n**Change required:**\n```yaml\nupdateStrategy:\n  type: RollingUpdate\n  rollingUpdate:\n    partition: 0\n```\n\nUse `partition` to control the rollout: set `partition: 2` to update only `es-cluster-2` first, verify, then decrement to 1, then 0. This replicates the manual OnDelete workflow with automatic re-scheduling.\n\n### 3.3 HIGH — JVM Heap Sizing\n**Current state:** `-Xms512m -Xmx512m`. Memory limit is 2Gi; the heap is only 25% of the container limit.  \n**Elasticsearch guidance:** Heap should be ~50% of available RAM, capped at 31GB (to stay below the JVM compressed oops boundary).\n\n**Change required (ES_JAVA_OPTS in StatefulSet env):**\n```\n-Xms1g -Xmx1g\n```\nThis brings heap to 50% of the 2Gi limit. If the memory limit is raised in a future iteration, scale proportionally.\n\n### 3.4 MEDIUM — PVC Capacity\n**Current state:** 5Gi per node. With three nodes and the `audit-index` having 3 shards + 1 replica, total data is replicated and distributed. 5Gi is very small for production use; disk watermarks will trigger at 85%/4.25Gi used.\n\n**Change required:** Expand PVCs to an appropriate size before the index grows. This requires resizing the underlying PersistentVolumes (StorageClass must support volume expansion) and patching the PVC spec. Plan sizing based on projected audit log volume over the ILM retention window.\n\n### 3.5 MEDIUM — Role Separation\n**Current state:** Every node holds master, data, and ingest roles simultaneously. In a 3-node cluster, quorum requires all nodes to be available for master elections; a data-heavy workload on any node can starve the master thread.\n\n**Recommended target topology for production:**\n- 3 dedicated master-eligible nodes (no data role, no ingest role)\n- 3+ dedicated data nodes (hot tier) with `node.attr.tier: hot`\n- Optionally 1–2 ingest/coordinating nodes\n\nFor a small cluster where separate master nodes are not feasible, at minimum ensure the JVM heap and CPU limits on the current mixed nodes are sufficient so a GC pause on a data node does not lose quorum.\n\n### 3.6 MEDIUM — audit-index Shard Routing\n**Current state:**\n```json\n\"routing\": {\n  \"allocation\": {\n    \"include\": {\"_tier_preference\": \"data_content\"},\n    \"require\": {\"tier\": \"hot\"}\n  }\n}\n```\nThe `require.tier: hot` constraint hard-pins all shards to nodes with `node.attr.tier=hot`. Currently all nodes have this attribute, so all shards are STARTED.\n\n**Risk during upgrade:** If a node restarts without the `tier: hot` attribute (e.g., if the ConfigMap is modified accidentally), shards on that node will become unassigned.\n\n**Recommended action:** Before the upgrade, verify the attribute is present on all replacement pod specs. If role separation is adopted (item 3.5), only hot-tier data nodes should carry this attribute; the `require` constraint must then be kept in sync with the new node roles. Do not change the index setting itself without a full allocation review.\n\n### 3.7 LOW — mmap Disabled\n**Current state:** `node.store.allow_mmap: false`. This was set to avoid `vm.max_map_count` kernel parameter requirements in the Kubernetes environment.\n\n**Performance impact:** Elasticsearch defaults to mmap for the MergedSegmentReader. Disabling it forces the NIO file channel fallback, which is slower for read-heavy workloads.\n\n**Change required:** Set `vm.max_map_count=262144` via a DaemonSet init container or a node-level `sysctl` configuration (`privileged: true`, `sysctls: [{name: vm.max_map_count, value: \"262144\"}]`), then remove `node.store.allow_mmap: false` from elasticsearch.yml.\n\n### 3.8 LOW — Snapshot Lifecycle Management\n**Current state:** No snapshot repository configured. No SLM policy. There is no automated backup.\n\n**Change required:**\n1. Register a snapshot repository (S3, GCS, Azure Blob, or shared filesystem).\n2. Create an SLM policy to take daily snapshots with a retention window matching compliance requirements.\n3. Verify the first snapshot succeeds before any version upgrade begins.\n\n### 3.9 LOW — audit-index ILM Policy\n**Current state:** `audit-index` has no ILM policy assigned. It will grow unbounded until manually deleted.\n\n**Change required:** Assign an appropriate ILM policy (e.g., the built-in `180-days-default`, or a custom policy matching the retention SLA) via an index template that matches the `audit-*` pattern.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Version Upgrade Procedure (Rolling)\n\nThe following steps assume the pre-upgrade checklist in Section 2 is complete and security (Section 3.1) has already been enabled.\n\n### Step 1 — Snapshot\n```\nPOST /_snapshot/<repo>/pre-upgrade-snapshot\nGET /_snapshot/<repo>/pre-upgrade-snapshot/_status\n```\nDo not proceed until status is SUCCESS.\n\n### Step 2 — Disable shard allocation (prevent thrashing during rolling restart)\n```\nPUT /_cluster/settings\n{\"persistent\": {\"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": \"primaries\"}}\n```\n\n### Step 3 — Update the StatefulSet image\n```\nkubectl -n elasticsearch set image statefulset/es-cluster \\\n  elasticsearch=docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:<target-version>\n```\n\n### Step 4 — Roll pods one at a time (if updateStrategy remains OnDelete)\nFor each pod from the highest ordinal down (es-cluster-2, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-0):\n```\nkubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-<N>\nkubectl -n elasticsearch wait pod/es-cluster-<N> --for=condition=Ready --timeout=300s\nkubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- \\\n  curl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cat/nodes?v\"\n```\nWait for all shards to recover (GREEN) before deleting the next pod.\n\n### Step 5 — Re-enable shard allocation\n```\nPUT /_cluster/settings\n{\"persistent\": {\"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": null}}\n```\n\n### Step 6 — Verify cluster health\n```\nGET /_cluster/health?wait_for_status=green&timeout=60s\nGET /_cat/nodes?v\nGET /_cat/indices?v\n```\n\n### Step 7 — Post-upgrade snapshot\nTake a second snapshot tagged `post-upgrade-<version>`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Risk Register\n\n| ID | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| R1 | Security disabled — data exposed in transit and at rest | CRITICAL | Enable xpack.security before production traffic is added (Section 3.1) |\n| R2 | No backups — data unrecoverable after cluster failure | HIGH | Configure snapshot repository + SLM before upgrade (Section 3.8) |\n| R3 | OnDelete strategy — stale pods after image update | HIGH | Switch to RollingUpdate or establish a documented manual pod-rotation runbook (Section 3.2) |\n| R4 | JVM heap undersized — increased GC pressure | MEDIUM | Raise to -Xms1g -Xmx1g (Section 3.3) |\n| R5 | 58 pending tasks at inspection — unknown cause | MEDIUM | Investigate and resolve before upgrade; cluster may have internal contention |\n| R6 | PVC at 5Gi — flood-stage watermark at ~4.75Gi | MEDIUM | Expand PVCs before volume fills (Section 3.4) |\n| R7 | All nodes are master-eligible — quorum fragile | MEDIUM | Plan role separation; at minimum do not let a single node become unavailable without a quorum plan (Section 3.5) |\n| R8 | mmap disabled — read performance degraded | LOW | Fix vm.max_map_count at node level (Section 3.7) |\n| R9 | audit-index has no ILM — unbounded growth | LOW | Assign ILM policy before index accumulates data (Section 3.9) |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Change Summary Table\n\n| # | Component | Change | Priority | Live State Preserved? |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 3.1 | elasticsearch.yml / Secrets | Enable xpack.security, HTTP TLS, transport TLS | CRITICAL | Yes — read-only plan |\n| 3.2 | StatefulSet updateStrategy | OnDelete → RollingUpdate | HIGH | Yes |\n| 3.3 | StatefulSet env ES_JAVA_OPTS | -Xms512m → -Xms1g | HIGH | Yes |\n| 3.4 | PVCs | Resize 5Gi → capacity-planned value | MEDIUM | Yes |\n| 3.5 | Node roles | Introduce role separation | MEDIUM | Yes |\n| 3.6 | audit-index routing | No change; maintain require.tier=hot | MEDIUM | Yes — no change |\n| 3.7 | Node OS / elasticsearch.yml | Enable mmap (vm.max_map_count) | LOW | Yes |\n| 3.8 | Snapshot repo + SLM | Create repository and daily policy | HIGH | Yes |\n| 3.9 | audit-index ILM | Assign ILM policy via index template | LOW | Yes |\n| 4.x | Image version | Roll 8.11.1 → <target> via Section 4 procedure | HIGH | Yes — rolling |\n\nAll changes listed above are **proposed only**. No modification has been made to the live cluster.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Approvals Required\n\n- [ ] SRE Lead sign-off on this plan\n- [ ] Security team review of Section 3.1 (certificate issuance process)\n- [ ] Data retention / compliance review of Section 3.9 (audit log ILM retention window)\n- [ ] Storage team confirmation that StorageClass supports PVC expansion (Section 3.4)\n- [ ] Change management ticket opened and approved before any kubectl apply'\n\necho \"Plan text composed\"","description":"Compose the migration plan text (dry run verification)"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1668,"cache_read_input_tokens":37673,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1668},"output_tokens":40,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"72158477-bdb4-4c96-ad02-c4ca72800a42","uuid":"32bc771f-f594-4af5-a14d-cedbd724f5e9","request_id":"req_011CcLD5HfeUStiXkrZWqNbc"}
