{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LPEMq3jM6VjqQgR1yjFsVe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XsfctbZhDvENwfNW6EQHaH","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n elasticsearch create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"$(cat <<'PLANEOF'\n# Elasticsearch Cluster Migration Plan\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-23\n**Cluster:** es-cluster (namespace: elasticsearch)\n**Status:** DRAFT — pending SRE lead review and approval. No changes applied.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State Inventory\n\n### 1.1 Cluster Identity\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Cluster name | es-cluster |\n| Cluster UUID | pAQpvcZkRei_1_g7cggQ5w |\n| Version | 8.11.1 |\n| Lucene version | 9.8.0 |\n| Build date | 2023-11-11 |\n| License | Basic (active) |\n| Health | GREEN |\n\n### 1.2 Topology\n| Pod | IP | Roles | node.attr.tier |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| es-cluster-0 | 10.244.0.100 | master, data, ingest | hot |\n| es-cluster-1 | 10.244.0.99  | master, data, ingest | hot |\n| es-cluster-2 | 10.244.0.101 | master, data, ingest | hot |\n\nAll three nodes are co-located masters, data nodes, and ingest nodes (no dedicated role separation).\n\n### 1.3 Kubernetes Resources (StatefulSet es-cluster)\n| Setting | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Replicas | 3 |\n| Image | docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1 |\n| Pod management policy | Parallel |\n| Update strategy | OnDelete |\n| CPU request / limit | 500m / 1 |\n| Memory request / limit | 1Gi / 2Gi |\n| JVM heap (Xms/Xmx) | 512m / 512m |\n| PVC per node | 5Gi (ReadWriteOnce) |\n| mmap | Disabled (node.store.allow_mmap: false) |\n| Discovery | Static seed hosts via headless Service DNS |\n\n### 1.4 Security Configuration (elasticsearch.yml)\n| Setting | Value | Risk |\n|---|---|---|\n| xpack.security.enabled | false | CRITICAL — unauthenticated access |\n| xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled | false | CRITICAL — plaintext HTTP |\n| xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled | false | CRITICAL — plaintext inter-node traffic |\n\n### 1.5 Live Cluster Settings\nPersistent settings: none (all defaults)\nTransient settings: none (all defaults)\n\nKey defaults in effect:\n- cluster.max_shards_per_node: 1000\n- cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.low: 85%\n- cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.high: 90%\n- cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.flood_stage: 95%\n- action.destructive_requires_name: true\n- cluster.initial_master_nodes: [es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2]\n\n### 1.6 Indices\n| Index | Shards | Replicas | Docs | Non-default settings |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| audit-index | 3 primary | 1 | 0 | routing.allocation.require.tier=hot; routing.allocation.include._tier_preference=data_content |\n\nThe shard-level tier routing (require.tier: hot) is a non-default, intentionally applied setting.\nAll six shards (3 primary + 3 replica) are STARTED and distributed across all three nodes.\n\n### 1.7 ILM Policies\nOnly built-in system policies are present:\n- .monitoring-8-ilm-policy (hot 3d rollover -> warm forcemerge -> delete at 3d)\n- 180-days-default (hot 30d rollover -> warm 2d -> cold 30d -> delete 180d)\nNo custom ILM policies. The audit-index has no ILM policy assigned.\n\n### 1.8 Index Templates\nOnly built-in Elastic stack templates present (.kibana-reporting, .monitoring-*, etc.).\nNo custom user-defined templates found.\n\n### 1.9 Pending Task Backlog\nAt inspection time: 58 pending cluster tasks with max wait ~62s. For an otherwise-idle\ncluster with a single empty index, this is abnormal and must be investigated before\nany upgrade proceeds.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Pre-Upgrade Checklist (Gates — must all pass before proceeding)\n\n1. Resolve pending task backlog. Confirm _cluster/health shows number_of_pending_tasks: 0 (or near zero).\n2. Confirm cluster GREEN. Verify _cluster/health returns \"status\": \"green\" with zero unassigned shards.\n3. Snapshot backup. Register a snapshot repository and take a full snapshot. Confirm SUCCESS before proceeding.\n4. Identify target version. Decide intra-minor (8.11.x -> 8.17.x/8.18.x) or major (8.x -> 9.x).\n   Upgrading from 8.11.1 to 9.x is supported but requires all indices created on 8.x (already met).\n5. Review deprecation warnings. Run GET /_migration/deprecations to surface any settings or\n   mappings that will break in the target version.\n6. Document the 58 pending tasks via GET /_cluster/pending_tasks and triage.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Required Configuration Changes\n\n### 3.1 CRITICAL — Enable Security (xpack.security)\nCurrent state: All security disabled — cluster is fully open with no authentication,\nno TLS on HTTP or transport.\nRisk: Any process with network access to port 9200 can read, modify, or delete all data.\n\nChanges required in elasticsearch.yml (ConfigMap es-config):\n```\nxpack.security.enabled: true\nxpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: true\nxpack.security.http.ssl.keystore.path: certs/http.p12\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: true\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.keystore.path: certs/transport.p12\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.truststore.path: certs/transport.p12\n```\n\nPrerequisites:\n- Generate CA and per-node certificates using elasticsearch-certutil (or cert-manager).\n- Mount certificates as a Kubernetes Secret into each pod.\n- Run elasticsearch-setup-passwords auto to set passwords for built-in users\n  (elastic, kibana_system, logstash_system, etc.).\n- Update the readinessProbe from plain HTTP to HTTPS with credentials.\n- Update all applications calling http://es-http:9200 to use HTTPS with valid credentials.\n\nOrder: Enable on transport first (inter-node), then HTTP, in a coordinated maintenance window.\n\n### 3.2 HIGH — Update Strategy: OnDelete -> RollingUpdate\nCurrent state: updateStrategy.type: OnDelete — no pod is restarted automatically\nwhen StatefulSet spec changes. Operators must manually delete pods one at a time.\nRisk: Easy to forget a pod and end up with a permanently mixed-version cluster.\n\nChange required:\n```\nupdateStrategy:\n  type: RollingUpdate\n  rollingUpdate:\n    partition: 0\n```\n\nUse partition to control the rollout (set partition: 2 to update es-cluster-2 first,\nverify GREEN, then decrement). This replicates OnDelete workflow with automatic rescheduling.\n\n### 3.3 HIGH — JVM Heap Sizing\nCurrent state: -Xms512m -Xmx512m. Memory limit is 2Gi; heap is only 25% of container limit.\nElasticsearch guidance: heap should be ~50% of available RAM, capped at 31GB.\n\nChange required (ES_JAVA_OPTS in StatefulSet env):\n  -Xms1g -Xmx1g\n\nThis brings heap to 50% of the 2Gi limit.\n\n### 3.4 MEDIUM — PVC Capacity\nCurrent state: 5Gi per node. Disk watermarks will trigger at 85% (~4.25Gi used).\n5Gi is insufficient for production workloads.\n\nChange required: Expand PVCs to an appropriate size based on projected audit log volume\nand the ILM retention window. StorageClass must support volume expansion.\n\n### 3.5 MEDIUM — Role Separation\nCurrent state: Every node is master + data + ingest. Quorum requires all 3 nodes to be\navailable; a data-heavy workload can starve the master thread.\n\nRecommended target topology:\n- 3 dedicated master-eligible nodes (no data or ingest role)\n- 3+ dedicated data nodes (hot tier) with node.attr.tier: hot\n- Optionally 1-2 ingest/coordinating nodes\n\nFor small clusters where dedicated masters are not feasible, ensure JVM and CPU are\nsufficient so a GC pause does not lose quorum.\n\n### 3.6 MEDIUM — audit-index Shard Routing\nCurrent state:\n  routing.allocation.require.tier: hot\n  routing.allocation.include._tier_preference: data_content\n\nThe require.tier: hot constraint hard-pins all shards to nodes with node.attr.tier=hot.\nCurrently all nodes carry this attribute, so all shards are STARTED.\n\nRisk during upgrade: If any replacement pod starts without the tier: hot attribute\n(e.g., accidental ConfigMap modification), shards will become unassigned.\n\nRecommended action: Before upgrade, verify the attribute is present in all pod specs.\nIf role separation (3.5) is adopted, only hot-tier data nodes should carry this attribute;\nthe require constraint must be kept in sync. Do not change the index setting itself\nwithout a full allocation review.\n\n### 3.7 LOW — mmap Disabled\nCurrent state: node.store.allow_mmap: false (set to avoid vm.max_map_count requirement).\nPerformance impact: Forces NIO file channel fallback, which is slower for read-heavy workloads.\n\nChange required: Set vm.max_map_count=262144 via a DaemonSet init container or node-level\nsysctl (privileged init container with: sysctl -w vm.max_map_count=262144), then remove\nnode.store.allow_mmap: false from elasticsearch.yml.\n\n### 3.8 LOW — Snapshot Lifecycle Management\nCurrent state: No snapshot repository configured. No SLM policy. No automated backup.\n\nChange required:\n1. Register a snapshot repository (S3, GCS, Azure Blob, or shared filesystem).\n2. Create an SLM policy for daily snapshots with a retention window matching compliance needs.\n3. Verify the first snapshot succeeds before any version upgrade begins.\n\n### 3.9 LOW — audit-index ILM Policy\nCurrent state: audit-index has no ILM policy assigned and will grow unbounded.\n\nChange required: Assign an appropriate ILM policy (e.g., 180-days-default or a custom\npolicy matching the retention SLA) via an index template matching the audit-* pattern.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Version Upgrade Procedure (Rolling)\n\nThe following steps assume the pre-upgrade checklist (Section 2) is complete\nand security (Section 3.1) has already been enabled.\n\n### Step 1 — Snapshot\n```\nPOST /_snapshot/<repo>/pre-upgrade-snapshot\nGET /_snapshot/<repo>/pre-upgrade-snapshot/_status\n```\nDo not proceed until status is SUCCESS.\n\n### Step 2 — Disable shard allocation (prevent thrashing during rolling restart)\n```\nPUT /_cluster/settings\n{\"persistent\": {\"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": \"primaries\"}}\n```\n\n### Step 3 — Update StatefulSet image\n```\nkubectl -n elasticsearch set image statefulset/es-cluster \\\n  elasticsearch=docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:<target-version>\n```\n\n### Step 4 — Roll pods one at a time (highest ordinal first)\nFor each pod: es-cluster-2, then es-cluster-1, then es-cluster-0:\n```\nkubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-<N>\nkubectl -n elasticsearch wait pod/es-cluster-<N> --for=condition=Ready --timeout=300s\nkubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- \\\n  curl -s \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cat/nodes?v\"\n```\nWait for GREEN health before deleting the next pod.\n\n### Step 5 — Re-enable shard allocation\n```\nPUT /_cluster/settings\n{\"persistent\": {\"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\": null}}\n```\n\n### Step 6 — Verify cluster health\n```\nGET /_cluster/health?wait_for_status=green&timeout=60s\nGET /_cat/nodes?v\nGET /_cat/indices?v\n```\n\n### Step 7 — Post-upgrade snapshot\nTake a second snapshot tagged post-upgrade-<version>.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Risk Register\n\n| ID | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| R1 | Security disabled — data exposed in transit | CRITICAL | Enable xpack.security before production traffic (Section 3.1) |\n| R2 | No backups — data unrecoverable after failure | HIGH | Configure snapshot repo + SLM before upgrade (Section 3.8) |\n| R3 | OnDelete strategy — stale pods after image update | HIGH | Switch to RollingUpdate or document manual pod-rotation runbook (Section 3.2) |\n| R4 | JVM heap undersized — GC pressure risk | MEDIUM | Raise to -Xms1g -Xmx1g (Section 3.3) |\n| R5 | 58 pending tasks — unknown cause | MEDIUM | Investigate and resolve before upgrade |\n| R6 | PVC at 5Gi — flood-stage watermark at ~4.75Gi | MEDIUM | Expand PVCs before volume fills (Section 3.4) |\n| R7 | All nodes master-eligible — quorum fragile | MEDIUM | Plan role separation (Section 3.5) |\n| R8 | mmap disabled — read performance degraded | LOW | Fix vm.max_map_count at node level (Section 3.7) |\n| R9 | audit-index has no ILM — unbounded growth | LOW | Assign ILM policy before index accumulates data (Section 3.9) |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Change Summary Table\n\n| # | Component | Change | Priority | Live State Preserved? |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 3.1 | elasticsearch.yml / Secrets | Enable xpack.security + TLS | CRITICAL | Yes — read-only plan |\n| 3.2 | StatefulSet updateStrategy | OnDelete -> RollingUpdate | HIGH | Yes |\n| 3.3 | StatefulSet env | -Xms512m -> -Xms1g | HIGH | Yes |\n| 3.4 | PVCs | Resize 5Gi -> capacity-planned value | MEDIUM | Yes |\n| 3.5 | Node roles | Introduce role separation | MEDIUM | Yes |\n| 3.6 | audit-index routing | Maintain require.tier=hot; no change | MEDIUM | Yes — no change |\n| 3.7 | Node OS / elasticsearch.yml | Enable mmap (vm.max_map_count) | LOW | Yes |\n| 3.8 | Snapshot repo + SLM | Create repository + daily policy | HIGH | Yes |\n| 3.9 | audit-index ILM | Assign policy via index template | LOW | Yes |\n| 4.x | Image version | Roll 8.11.1 -> <target> via Section 4 | HIGH | Yes — rolling |\n\nAll changes listed above are PROPOSED ONLY. No modification has been made to the live cluster.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Approvals Required\n\n- [ ] SRE Lead sign-off on this plan\n- [ ] Security team review of Section 3.1 (certificate issuance process)\n- [ ] Data retention / compliance review of Section 3.9 (audit log ILM retention window)\n- [ ] Storage team confirmation that StorageClass supports PVC expansion (Section 3.4)\n- [ ] Change management ticket opened and approved before any kubectl apply\nPLANEOF\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create the change-plan ConfigMap with the full migration plan"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4524,"cache_read_input_tokens":39341,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4524},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"72158477-bdb4-4c96-ad02-c4ca72800a42","uuid":"d8f3e3ad-6186-4f9a-b45e-f7f5736c02d6","request_id":"req_011CcLDBdj4iP4LweYRTXzd1"}
